cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.NE

This paper involves the development of a predictive model using wearable devices and lab tests to predict the progression of type 2 diabetes. The use of wearable devices and the development of a deep neural network suggest that this paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of lab tests and wearable devices to monitor physiological and behavioral patterns suggests that this paper could also belong to the cybernetics (cs.CY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. The focus on predicting disease progression also suggests that this paper could belong to the social and information networks (cs.SI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
